We recommended that the OIC-Municipal Treasurer require the Revenue Collection Clerk to submit the RAAF with Money Value, Invoice and Receipt of Accountable Forms from the date when the Revenue Collection Clerk handled the cash tickets and account the difference noted between the RCD and actual cash tickets on hand to properly establish her accountability. We also recommended that the OIC-Municipal Treasurer, henceforth, strictly monitor and control the purchases and issuances of accountable forms with money value, like cash tickets, by maintaining a permanent record book following the column headings required under Section 59(L) of the Local Treasury Manual. The Municipality is likewise required to devise their own system in the issuance of cash tickets to ensure proper control, accounting and audit. Control measures enumerated in Section 59(C) of the Local Treasury Manual include but not limited to the following:
(a) Stamping serial numbers or the name or logo of the Municipality at the back of the cash tickets before issuing to assigned collectors;
(b) Affixing of initials of collector and date of issuance in the cash tickets before issuance; and tearing off of cash tickets after collections have been received to avoid possible re-issuance.

