require coordination between the Municipal Accountant and the Acting General Services Officer towards the implementation of the perpetual inventory method in recording of supplies and materials and maintain the prescribed records to ensure proper accounting and promote better control in the receipt and issuance of supplies;

direct the Inventory Committee to conduct periodic physical inventories of supplies or property of the Municipal Government and prepare and submit the corresponding reports to the Audit Team not later than July 31 and January 31 of each year for the first and second semesters, respectively as mandated under Section 124 of the NGAS Manual for Local Government Units, Volume 1.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:

require the Inventory Committee to conduct a complete physical inventory of all properties of the Municipal Government and prepare and submit the corresponding reports to the Audit Team as mandated by the above provision;

require the designated Inventory Committee and Accounting Office to prioritize the reconciliation of property and accounting records of PPE accounts and ensure the discrepancies noted in the reconciliation of PPE records be immediately verified and adjusted accordingly.

